The Unicode module makes it easier to handle Unicode strings (UCS-2)
in a perl program.  The following is examples of use:

   use Unicode;

   $u = Unicode::utf8("this is a string");
   print $u->ucs2;
   print $u->latin1;
   print $u->utf8;

   print Unicode::latin1("naïve\n")->utf8;


